Court-Martial Convening Authorities

Section A. Court-Martial Convening Authorities

A.1. General courts- Under the authority of Article 22(a)(8) , UCMJ, the Secretary has designated the 
martial convening following commanding officers of the Coast Guard as general court-martial convening 
authorities  authorities:

a. Commandant of the Coast Guard;

b. Commander of any Coast Guard Area;

c. Commander of any Coast Guard District;

d. Deputy Commandant for Mission Support (DCMS);

e. Director of Operational Logistics (DOL);

f. Commanding Officer, Coast Guard Headquarters;

g. Superintendent, Coast Guard Academy;

h. Commander, Coast Guard Personnel Service Center (PSC); and

i. Commander, Coast Guard Force Readiness Command (FORCECOM).

j. Commander, Coast Guard Cyber Command (CGCYBERCOM)

A.2. Special courts- Under the authority of Article 23(a)(7), UCMJ, the Secretary has designated the 
martial convening following commanding officers of the Coast Guard as special court-martial convening 
authorities authorities:

a. Commanding Officers of all Coast Guard units, some of whom have specific 
statutory authority;

b. Commander of any Coast Guard Sector;

c. Commanding Officer, Staff Enlisted Personnel, at each Coast Guard Area;

d. Commanding Officer, Staff Enlisted Personnel, at each Coast Guard District;

e.  Commanding Officer, Enlisted Personnel, Coast Guard Academy;

f. Commanding Officer, Enlisted Personnel, Coast Guard Yard;

g. Commanding Officer, Military Personnel, National Pollution Funds Center;

h. Commanding Officer, Staff Enlisted Personnel, Coast Guard Force Readiness 
Command; and

i. Commanding Officer, Military Personnel, Coast Guard Command, Control, 
Communications, Computers, and Information Technology Center.

A.3. Training required Per Article 137, UCMJ, those with authority  to convene courts-m artial must receive 
for those with authority periodic training regarding the purpose and administration of the UCMJ. Periodic 
to convene training will be valid from the time received until the trainee is no longer in a billet with 
authority to convene courts-martial or 3 years, whichever comes first. Staff Judge 
Advocates will ensure that those with authority to convene courts-martial, within their 
area of responsibility, have completed the periodic training. The following courses 
include training blocks that fulfil the Article 137, UCMJ periodic training requirements:

g. Prospective Commanding Officer, Officer in Charge, Executive Officer and 
